        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I don't see any maintenance cost here\n\nEverything has maintenance cost. When you add a new feature you have to \nmake sure that it works with all existing features and will keep on \nworking as new features are added and old ones are removed. When the \nfeature relies on external code you have to make sure that you keep it \nup to date, that updates don't break anything and so on and so forth.\n\nI'm not one of the maintainers, so I don't get to decide what's worth \nits maintenance cost and what isn't, but IMO this feature adds nothing \nthat can't be already done and thus isn't worth its cost :).\n",
